âœ… 3. Install SQLite Plugin

Grafana does NOT support SQLite by default.
To connect olist.sqlite, you must install the plugin.

Step 3.1 â€” Open Command Prompt as Administrator

Press Start

Type cmd

Right-click â†’ Run as administrator

Step 3.2 â€” Navigate to Grafana installation directory
cd /d "C:\Program Files\GrafanaLabs\grafana"

Step 3.3 â€” Install SQLite plugin

Run:

bin\grafana-cli.exe plugins install frser-sqlite-datasource


If this plugin is not available, use the alternative:

bin\grafana-cli.exe plugins install marcusolsson-sqlite-datasource


Expected successful output:

âœ” Downloaded and extracted frser-sqlite-datasource successfully


(A small temp-file error is okay â€” plugin still installs.)

âœ… 4. Restart Grafana Service

Once plugin installation is complete, restart Grafana:

Option A â€” Command Prompt
